docs/architecture.md:5:PopDAM3 is a hybrid cloud/on-premises Digital Asset Manager for licensed consumer-product art. A React/Vite frontend (served via nginx on a Coolify-managed VPS) connects to a Supabase PostgreSQL database and twelve Deno edge functions (project ID `ryltkzzernhwnojzouyb`). A Node.js bridge agent running in Docker on a Synology NAS scans the filesystem, generates thumbnails, and pushes them to DigitalOcean Spaces; a separate Windows render agent handles Illustrator files. A persistent Railway cloud worker runs AI tagging, ERP enrichment, and style group rebuilds by polling a job queue stored in the `admin_config` table. The same Docker image serves both PopDAM (`dam.designflow.app`) and PopSG (`sg.designflow.app`); the active mode is determined at runtime by hostname.
docs/architecture.md:34:**What it does:** registers with `agent-api` using a one-time pairing code, then enters a continuous loop. Receives commands via Supabase Realtime (instant) or heartbeat polling (fallback every 30 s). On a scan command: validates roots → walks the NAS filesystem → computes quick hash (first 64 KB + last 64 KB + file size) → generates thumbnails using MuPDF and Sharp → uploads thumbnails to DigitalOcean Spaces → calls `agent-api` to ingest metadata into Supabase. Also handles PDF text sampling, AI sentinel file detection, PopSG style guide crawls, and self-update.
docs/architecture.md:64:1. Admin triggers a scan from the web UI (Settings → Agents) or the bridge agent receives a `SCAN_REQUEST` from `admin_config`.
docs/architecture.md:66:3. Bridge agent walks the NAS filesystem, hashing files (first/last 64 KB + size). Files already in Supabase with matching hash and path → noop; matching hash but different path → move (preserves tags, writes `asset_path_history`).
docs/architecture.md:68:5. Bridge agent calls `POST /agent/batch-ingest` on `agent-api` with up to 100 files per batch. `agent-api` upserts rows into `assets`, setting `relative_path` (canonical POSIX, no leading slash), `quick_hash`, `modified_at` (filesystem mtime, never server time), `thumbnail_url`, and derived metadata.
docs/architecture.md:70:7. Bridge agent calls `POST /agent/scan-progress` throughout and reports completion.
docs/architecture.md:83:2. Admin-api writes a `sibling_scan_request_*` row to `admin_config`.
docs/architecture.md:84:3. Bridge agent claims the request via `agent-api` route `claim-sibling-scan`, walks the specified folder looking for sibling JPG/PNG/eligible PDF files alongside existing assets, and reports results through `complete-sibling-scan`.
docs/architecture.md:86:5. Admin-api handler (`sibling-scan-handlers.ts`) ingests confirmed siblings into `assets`.
